This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D shape analysis and understanding using point clouds. It also involves deep learning networks for feature extraction and aggregation, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel deep learning network for learning discriminative shape representation. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also likely as the paper involves developing a network that can learn spatial relationships among local regions, which is an important aspect of AI. 

The graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with 3D shape analysis and understanding, which is a common topic in computer graphics. 

Finally, the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not involve any language processing tasks.
